 favor of Halitza. The second shows, on the basis of the Book of Tobit, how aspects of marriage rituals can be traced into rabbinic times. Finally, an analysis of the marriage of the Samaritan woman in John 4:16-18 completes the volume.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jun 2020) 0aJewish marriage customs and rites. 0aLevirate. 4aEheschließung. 4aFrühjudentum. 4aLevirat. 4aTobitbuch. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Studies / Old Testament.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theology, Religion, Judaism 2014z9783110370409oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831103855950 cprintz978311033992540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311034080840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110340808423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110340808.jpg  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGFb2014  aZDB-23-DGGb2014